      { title: "S2: BUS", color: SC[2], params: [
        { key: "propHeating_kW", label: "Prop Heating", unit: "kW", min: 0, max: 10, step: 0.5 },
        { key: "tpvInputPower_kW", label: "TPV Input", unit: "kW", min: 0, max: 30, step: 0.5 },
        { key: "tpvBlockTemp_K", label: "TPV Block Temp", unit: "K", min: 400, max: 800, step: 10 },
        { key: "tpvEfficiency", label: "TPV Efficiency", unit: "", min: 0.05, max: 0.35, step: 0.01 },
        { key: "attitudeLouver_W", label: "Attitude Louvers", unit: "W", min: 0, max: 1000, step: 10 },
      ]},
      { title: "S3: RADIATOR", color: SC[3], params: [
        { key: "numTiles", label: "Tiles", unit: "", min: 4, max: 100, step: 1 },
        { key: "tileArea_m2", label: "Tile Area", unit: "m²", min: 5, max: 50, step: 1 },
        { key: "radTemp_K", label: "Radiator Temp", unit: "K", min: 250, max: 500, step: 5 },
        { key: "hotGateFrac", label: "Hot Gate Frac", unit: "", min: 0.01, max: 0.3, step: 0.01 },
        { key: "coneAngle_deg", label: "Cone Angle", unit: "°", min: 5, max: 45, step: 1 },
        { key: "dockingTiles", label: "Docking Tiles", unit: "", min: 0, max: 10, step: 1 },
      ]},
    ].map(({ title, color, params: ps }) => (
      <div key={title} style={{ marginBottom: 10 }}>
        <div style={{ fontSize: 9, color, fontWeight: 700, letterSpacing: 0.5, marginBottom: 6 }}>{title}</div>
        {ps.map(p => <Sl key={p.key} {...p} value={params[p.key]} onChange={setP} accent={color} />)}
      </div>
    ))}
  </>}

  {/* ━━━ SCALING ━━━ */}
  {tab === "scale" && <>
    <div style={{ background: "#0d1520", border: "1px solid #1a2a3a", borderRadius: 4, padding: "8px 10px", marginBottom: 10 }}>
      <div style={{ fontSize: 9, color: "#3a5a6a", letterSpacing: 0.5, marginBottom: 6 }}>
        REUSE SATURATION vs POWER
      </div>
      {/* Bar chart showing saturation at different scales */}
      {[50, 100, 200, 500, 1000].map(kw => {
        const sim = computePlatform({ ...params, totalPower_kW: kw });
        const sat = sim.reuseSaturation;
        const isCurrent = kw === params.totalPower_kW;
        return (
          <div key={kw} style={{ marginBottom: 4 }}>
            <div style={{ display: "flex", justifyContent: "space-between", fontSize: 8, color: "#4a6a7a", marginBottom: 1 }}>
              <span style={{ color: isCurrent ? "#00ccaa" : "#5a7a8a", fontWeight: isCurrent ? 700 : 400 }}>
                {kw} kW {isCurrent ? "◄" : ""}
              </span>
              <span>{pct(sat)} reused | {fW(sim.totalReuse_W)}</span>
            </div>
            <div style={{ height: 8, background: "#0a0e14", borderRadius: 2, overflow: "hidden" }}>
              <div style={{
                width: `${sat * 100}%`, height: "100%",
                background: sat > 0.2 ? "#00ccaa" : sat > 0.1 ? "#ffaa44" : "#ff4444",
                borderRadius: 2, transition: "width 0.3s",
              }} />
            </div>
          </div>
        );
      })}
    </div>

    {/* Scaling issues */}
    {plat.scalingIssues.length > 0 && (
      <div style={{ background: "#0d1520", border: "1px solid #ff444430", borderRadius: 4, padding: "8px 10px", marginBottom: 10 }}>
        <div style={{ fontSize: 9, color: "#ff4444", fontWeight: 700, marginBottom: 6 }}>SCALING WALLS</div>
        {plat.scalingIssues.map((si, i) => (
          <div key={i} style={{ marginBottom: 6, display: "flex", gap: 6 }}>
            <div style={{
              width: 8, height: 8, borderRadius: "50%", marginTop: 3, flexShrink: 0,
              background: si.severity === "critical" ? "#ff4444" : "#ffaa44",
              boxShadow: `0 0 6px ${si.severity === "critical" ? "#ff444460" : "#ffaa4460"}`,
            }} />
            <div>
              <div style={{ fontSize: 10, color: si.severity === "critical" ? "#ff6644" : "#ffaa44", fontWeight: 600 }}>{si.issue}</div>
              <div style={{ fontSize: 9, color: "#4a6a7a" }}>{si.detail}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    )}

    {plat.scalingIssues.length === 0 && (
      <div style={{ background: "#00ccaa08", border: "1px solid #00ccaa20", borderRadius: 4, padding: "8px 10px", marginBottom: 10 }}>
        <div style={{ fontSize: 10, color: "#00ccaa", fontWeight: 600 }}>
          Within single-vehicle envelope — no scaling walls hit
        </div>
      </div>
    )}

    <div style={{ background: "#0d1520", border: "1px solid #1a2a3a", borderRadius: 4, padding: "8px 10px", fontSize: 9, color: "#5a7a8a", lineHeight: 1.6 }}>
      <b style={{ color: "#ff6644" }}>WHY 1MW BREAKS: </b>
      Single-phase loop pressure drop exceeds COTS pump limits. Thermal customers (heaters, prop, TPV)
      saturate — reuse ratio crashes. Hot gate coherence needs active management.
      Radiator structural mass exceeds single-vehicle deploy.
      Solution: distribute across loosely coupled swarm nodes.
    </div>

    <div style={{ marginTop: 10 }}>
      <Sl key="totalPower_kW" k="totalPower_kW" label="Total Power" unit="kW" min={10} max={2000} step={10}
        value={params.totalPower_kW} onChange={setP} accent="#ff6644" />
    </div>
  </>}

  {/* ━━━ SWARM ━━━ */}
  {tab === "swarm" && <>
    <div style={{ background: "#0d1520", border: "1px solid #00ccaa25", borderRadius: 4, padding: "10px", marginBottom: 10 }}>
      <div style={{ fontSize: 10, color: "#00ccaa", fontWeight: 700, marginBottom: 8 }}>
        500m² THERMAL API
      </div>
      <div style={{ fontSize: 9, color: "#5a7a8a", lineHeight: 1.6, marginBottom: 8 }}>
        The radiator array isn't dumb metal. It's an interface serving multiple consumers:
      </div>

      {[
        { name: "Compute Cooling", capacity: fW(plat.P_final_dump), desc: "Primary thermal dump for payload", color: SC[1], pct: ((plat.P_final_dump / plat.P_waste) * 100).toFixed(0) },
        { name: "Housekeeping", capacity: fW(plat.S1_reuse_W + plat.P_prop_heating), desc: "Eclipse survival + prop conditioning", color: SC[2], pct: (((plat.S1_reuse_W + plat.P_prop_heating) / plat.P_waste) * 100).toFixed(0) },
        { name: "Signaling", capacity: fW(plat.P_beacon_total) + " + " + plat.beaconBitrate_bps + " bps", desc: "Directed IR beacon + nav data", color: SC[3], pct: ((plat.P_beacon_total / plat.P_waste) * 100).toFixed(1) },
        { name: "Diagnostics", capacity: plat.diagnosticTiles + " tiles monitored", desc: "Thermal health → workload throttle", color: "#4488ff", pct: "—" },
        { name: "Docking Support", capacity: fW(plat.dockingCapacity_W), desc: `${params.dockingTiles} tiles for visiting craft`, color: "#cc66ff", pct: ((plat.dockingCapacity_W / plat.P_waste) * 100).toFixed(0) },
        { name: "Calibration", capacity: "Known IR signature", desc: "Sensor alignment reference", color: SC[4], pct: "—" },
      ].map(({ name, capacity, desc, color, pct }, i) => (
        <div key={i} style={{ display: "flex", gap: 8, marginBottom: 6, alignItems: "flex-start" }}>
          <div style={{
            width: 30, textAlign: "center", fontSize: 9, color, fontWeight: 700, flexShrink: 0, marginTop: 1,
          }}>{pct}%</div>
          <div style={{ flex: 1 }}>
            <div style={{ display: "flex", justifyContent: "space-between" }}>
              <span style={{ fontSize: 10, color, fontWeight: 600 }}>{name}</span>
              <span style={{ fontSize: 9, color: "#4a6a7a" }}>{capacity}</span>
            </div>
            <div style={{ fontSize: 8, color: "#3a4a5a" }}>{desc}</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    {/* Swarm interactions */}
    <div style={{ background: "#0d1520", border: "1px solid #ffaa4425", borderRadius: 4, padding: "10px", marginBottom: 10 }}>
      <div style={{ fontSize: 10, color: "#ffaa44", fontWeight: 700, marginBottom: 8 }}>SWARM INTERACTIONS</div>

      {[
        { name: "Thermal Leasing", desc: "Ground stations schedule your beacon window → you get priority compute beam time in return. Each beacon slot is a tradeable resource.", color: "#00ccaa" },
        { name: "Formation Heat Share", desc: "Neighbor vehicles dock cold plates to your docking tiles during their eclipse. Your waste heat is their survival.", color: "#ff8844" },
        { name: "Depot Transient Dump", desc: "Orbital depots clamp on during high-workload bursts, absorbing thermal spikes your radiators can't handle alone.", color: "#4488ff" },
        { name: "Swarm Calibration", desc: "Neighbors use your known IR signature as attitude reference. Your dump radiation is their sensor calibration source.", color: "#8866cc" },
      ].map(({ name, desc, color }, i) => (
        <div key={i} style={{ marginBottom: 8 }}>
          <div style={{ fontSize: 10, color, fontWeight: 600, marginBottom: 2 }}>{name}</div>
          <div style={{ fontSize: 9, color: "#5a7a8a", lineHeight: 1.5 }}>{desc}</div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div style={{
      background: "#00ccaa06", border: "1px solid #00ccaa15", borderRadius: 4,
      padding: "8px 10px", fontSize: 9, color: "#5a8a7a", lineHeight: 1.6,
    }}>
      <b style={{ color: "#00ccaa" }}>ENDGAME: </b>
      Every m² of radiator has a thermal API. Utility/kg scales with number of services, not area.
      Adding a swarm neighbor doesn't require more radiator — it requires more scheduling intelligence.
      The 1MW scaling wall dissolves into N × 100kW nodes that trade thermal capacity like a market.
    </div>
  </>}

  <div style={{ fontSize: 7, color: "#1a2a3a", textAlign: "center", padding: 10 }}>
    Thermopylae Platform · 4-Stage Joule Lifecycle
  </div>
</div>
```

);
}
